bilingual.source: It had sharp teeth, so I was happy to be up the tower.
bilingual.target: 它有锋利的牙齿，所以我很高兴在塔上。

bilingual.source: But Fox grabbed the fish in his sharp teeth and ran off with it.
bilingual.target: 但狐狸用锋利的牙齿抓住鱼跑了。

bilingual.source: He lowered his walking stick, and the tiger used its sharp claws to scramble up.
bilingual.target: 他放下拐杖，老虎用它锋利的爪子爬了上来。

bilingual.source: They then damaged the mask even more when they removed extra glue with sharp tools.

bilingual.source: You need a sharp razor to shave.
bilingual.target: 你需要一把锋利的剃刀来剃胡子。

bilingual.source: He hew the tree with a sharp axe.

bilingual.target: 鳄鱼有非常锋利的牙齿。

bilingual.source: He held a sharp weapon in his hand.
bilingual.target: 他手里拿着一把锋利的武器。

bilingual.source: Use a sharp tool to pru the bushes.
bilingual.target: 使用锋利的工具来修剪灌木丛。

bilingual.source: Use a sharp knife to pare the apple.
bilingual.target: 使用锋利的刀来削皮苹果。

list.abstract: 夏普（Sharp Corporation，シャープ株式会社），是一家日本的电气及电子公司，1912年由早川德次在日本东京创立，总部位于日本大阪，吴柏勋任社长、执行役员兼CEO。 公司的主要业务包括电气通信机器、电子产品等的制造，主要产品有冷藏库、小型调理机器、加湿器、蓄电池、携带电话机等。 夏普公司2022财年（2022年4月至2023年3月）合并财报，净亏损2608亿日元（约合人民币135亿元）。

sharp
1998年《YES》，1999年第二张《tell me,tell me》，2000年第三张《好棒！》，2001年第四张《Sweet》以及2002年的唱片《我的嘴唇如热咖啡...》。通过各种风格的舞曲来表现自己的一支四人男女组合，这就是s#arp.

yingyinNormal.en: A good,sharp cleaver is always useful.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一把锋利的切肉刀总是很管用。

yingyinNormal.en: For your information, it's a card sharp, not a card shark.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我老实告诉你好了，是赌棍，不是老千。

yingyinNormal.en: Man, that is sharp. That must have cost you quite a few doubloons.
yingyinNormal.zh: 天呐，真时髦，你一定花了不少达布隆（古西班牙金币）吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Did he have no more teeth? He still had teeth, just no longer sharp.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他的牙都掉光了吗？他的牙还在只是不再如以前般锋利了。

yingyinNormal.en: Put this pencil over here. Sharp. Thanks to the machine we saw earlier.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们把铅笔放在这里。削得很尖，刚才的小玩意挺管用。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah. What else would I be dreaming about? Careful! That soup is sharp.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是啊，不然我还能梦什么？当心，面汤很扎嘴！

yingyinNormal.en: You're working for Jackie Sharp now? No. Just friends. Just friends, huh? Yeah.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你现在为杰姬·夏普工作了。不，只是朋友。只是朋友吗？嗯。

yingyinNormal.en: The road there leads through the sharp mountains and deep ravines of District 2.
yingyinNormal.zh: 通往第2区的是峥嵘山势和深沟险壑。

yingyinNormal.en: Very nice. Okay, looks like you got this. Very good. Sharp turn! No! Look out! No!
yingyinNormal.zh: 很好，看上去你学会了，很好哦，转弯！转弯！不！小心！

yingyinNormal.en: So couldn't you go back to it, Will? I mean, clearly you're still sharp as a tack. Dad!
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不能恢复到以前的状态了吗，威尔？虽说你依然非常厉害。爸爸！

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, that's a sharp jacket you've got on today. Oh, thanks. Wait. What are you doing here?
yingyinNormal.zh: 嘿，你今天穿得够显眼的啊。哦，谢谢。什么？你来这儿干嘛？

yingyinNormal.en: Your mind seems sharp as ever, Robert. Except for the fact that I can't remember your name right now.
yingyinNormal.zh: 看来你的头脑还像过去一样清醒，罗伯特。除了我现在想不起来你叫什么.

yingyinNormal.en: All right, this is it. This is it. Okay, look sharp. Luke, what's on your face? I don't know. What color is it?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，快点，快点，看着精神点儿，卢克，你脸上是什么？我不知道，什么颜色的？

yingyinNormal.en: Danton and Sharp corroborated. Oh, yes. Two people with very big chips on their shoulders, fabricating all this nonsense to justify their infidelity.
yingyinNormal.zh: 丹顿和夏普证实了此事。是吗？这两个人和我有很深的宿怨，无非是想给他们的出轨编个借口罢了。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, If I can find something sharp in here and poke a hole in the glove of my EVA suit. I could use the escaping air as a thruster and fly towards you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果我能找到一个尖锐物，我可以在我的宇航服上戳一个洞，然后就能用溢出的气体的当作助推然后飞过去找你。

yingyinNormal.en: You keep saying the White House isn't speaking about this. I am sitting right here talking to you. Not Remy Danton or Jackie Sharp. Or Lucas Goodwin, either.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你总说白宫不就此事发言。但我正坐在这里跟你说话，不是雷米·丹顿或杰姬·夏普，也不是卢卡斯·古德温。

examination_example.sentence: Playing an instrument or singing can help us do better in school and keep our brain <highlight>sharp</highlight> (敏锐的) as we get older.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 演奏乐器或唱歌可以帮助我们在学校取得更好的成绩，并随着年龄的增长保持大脑的敏锐。

examination_example.sentence: He felt a <highlight>sharp</highlight> pain in his knee.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他感到膝盖一阵剧痛。

sense_info_list.zh: 清楚明确的; 清晰的

examination_example.sentence: If you're happy, your mind will become livelier and your memory will become <highlight>sharper</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你快乐，你的思维会变得更活跃，你的记忆会变得更清晰。
